Kafka-streamingsource.Name: Kafka
Kafka-streamingsource.Description:
Kafka streaming source. Emits a record with the schema specified by the user. If no schema
is specified, it will emit a record with two fields: 'key' (nullable string) and 'message'
(bytes). This plugin uses kafka 0.10.2 java apis.

Encryptor-transform.Name: Encryptor
Encryptor-transform.Description:
Encrypts one or more fields in input records using a java keystore 
that must be present on all nodes of the cluster.

XMLToJSON-transform.Name: XMLToJSON
XMLToJSON-transform.Description:
Accepts a field that contains a properly-formatted XML string and 
outputs a properly-formatted JSON string version of the data. This is 
meant to be used with the Javascript transform for the parsing of 
complex XML documents into parts. Once the XML is a JSON string, you 
can convert it into a Javascript object using:

Excel-batchsource.Name: Excel
Excel-batchsource.Description: The Excel plugin provides user the ability to read data from one or more Excel file(s).

S3-batchsink.Name: S3
S3-batchsink.Description:
This sink is used whenever you need to write to Amazon S3 in various formats. For example,
you might want to create daily snapshots of a database by reading the entire contents of a
table, writing to this sink, and then other programs can analyze the contents of the
specified file.

Window-windower.Name: Window
Window-windower.Description: The Window plugin is used to window a part of a streaming pipeline.

PySparkProgram-sparkprogram.Name: PySparkProgram
PySparkProgram-sparkprogram.Description: Executes user-provided Spark code in Python.

Postgres-batchsource.Name: Postgres
Postgres-batchsource.Description:
Reads from a PostgreSQL using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

Repartitioner-sparkcompute.Name: Repartitioner
Repartitioner-sparkcompute.Description: This plugins re-partitions a Spark RDD.

Spanner-batchsource.Name: Spanner
Spanner-batchsource.Description:
This source reads from a Google Cloud Spanner table.
Cloud Spanner is a fully managed, mission-critical, relational database service that offers transactional
consistency at global scale, schemas, SQL (ANSI 2011 with extensions),
and automatic, synchronous replication for high availability.

FTP-batchsource.Name: FTP
FTP-batchsource.Description:
Batch source for an FTP or SFTP source. Prefix of the path ('ftp://...' or 'sftp://...') determines the source server
type, either FTP or SFTP.

KVTable-batchsink.Name: KVTable
KVTable-batchsink.Description:
Writes records to a KeyValueTable, using configurable fields from input records as the
key and value.

Kafka-batchsink.Name: Kafka
Kafka-batchsink.Description:
Kafka sink that allows you to write events into CSV or JSON to kafka.
Plugin has the capability to push the data to a Kafka topic. It can also be
configured to partition events being written to kafka based on a configurable key. 
The sink can also be configured to operate in sync or async mode and apply different
compression types to events. This plugin uses kafka 0.10.2 java apis.

Bigtable-batchsink.Name: Bigtable
Bigtable-batchsink.Description:
This sink writes data to Google Cloud Bigtable.
Cloud Bigtable is Google's NoSQL Big Data database service. 
It's the same database that powers many core Google services, including Search, Analytics, Maps, and Gmail.

DatabaseQuery-postaction.Name: DatabaseQuery
DatabaseQuery-postaction.Description:
Runs a database query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

XMLMultiParser-transform.Name: XMLMultiParser
XMLMultiParser-transform.Description:
The XML Multi Parser Transform uses XPath to extract fields from an XML document. It will generate records from
the children of the element specified by the XPath. If there is some error parsing the document or building the record,
the problematic input record will be dropped.

Database-batchsource.Name: Database
Database-batchsource.Description:
Reads from a database using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

Distinct-batchaggregator.Name: Distinct
Distinct-batchaggregator.Description:
De-duplicates input records so that all output records are distinct.
Can optionally take a list of fields, which will project out all other fields and perform a distinct on just those fields.

Kudu-batchsource.Name: Kudu
Kudu-batchsource.Description: CDAP Plugin for reading data from Apache Kudu table.

KafkaAlerts-alertpublisher.Name: KafkaAlerts
KafkaAlerts-alertpublisher.Description:
Kafka Alert Publisher that allows you to publish alerts to kafka as json objects.
The plugin internally uses kafka producer apis to publish alerts. 
The plugin allows to specify kafka topic to use for publishing and other additional
kafka producer properties. This plugin uses kafka 0.10.2 java apis.

GCSFile-batchsource.Name: GCSFile
GCSFile-batchsource.Description: This plugin reads objects from a path in a Google Cloud Storage bucket.

AzureDataLakeStore-batchsource.Name: AzureDataLakeStore
AzureDataLakeStore-batchsource.Description:
Azure Data Lake Store Batch Source reads data from Azure Data Lake Store files and converts it into 
StructuredRecord.

GooglePublisher-batchsink.Name: GooglePublisher
GooglePublisher-batchsink.Description:
This sink writes to a Google Cloud Pub/Sub topic.
Cloud Pub/Sub brings the scalability, flexibility, and reliability of enterprise message-oriented
middleware to the cloud. By providing many-to-many, asynchronous messaging that decouples senders and receivers,
it allows for secure and highly available communication between independently written applications.

DateTransform-transform.Name: DateTransform
DateTransform-transform.Description: This transform takes a date in either a unix timestamp or a string, and converts it to a formatted string. (Macro-enabled)

Conditional-condition.Name: Conditional
Conditional-condition.Description:
A control flow plugin that allows conditional execution within
pipelines. The conditions are specified as expressions and the
variables could include values specified as runtime arguments of
the pipeline, token from plugins prior to the condition and global
that includes global information about pipeline like stage, pipeline,
logical start time and plugin.

FastFilter-transform.Name: FastFilter
FastFilter-transform.Description: Filters out messages based on a specified criteria.

SqlServer-action.Name: SqlServer
SqlServer-action.Description: Action that runs a SQL Server command.

DynHBase-batchsink.Name: DynHBase
DynHBase-batchsink.Description: This plugin supports writing dynamic schemas record to local or remote HBase Table. In addition to writing dynamic schema tables, it also support regular structured records to be written to Tables.

AzureBlobStore-batchsource.Name: AzureBlobStore
AzureBlobStore-batchsource.Description: Batch source to use Microsoft Azure Blob Storage as a source.

KinesisSink-batchsink.Name: KinesisSink
KinesisSink-batchsink.Description: Kinesis sink that outputs to a specified Amazon Kinesis Stream.

Kudu-batchsink.Name: Kudu
Kudu-batchsink.Description: CDAP Plugin for ingesting data into Apache Kudu. Plugin can be configured for both batch and real-time pipelines.

Postgres-batchsink.Name: Postgres
Postgres-batchsink.Description: Writes records to a PostgreSQL table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

SpeechToText-transform.Name: SpeechToText
SpeechToText-transform.Description: This plugin converts audio files to text by using Google Cloud Speech-to-Text.

Bigtable-batchsource.Name: Bigtable
Bigtable-batchsource.Description:
This source reads data from Google Cloud Bigtable.
Cloud Bigtable is Google's NoSQL Big Data database service. 
It's the same database that powers many core Google services, including Search, Analytics, Maps, and Gmail.

FTPPut-action.Name: FTPPut
FTPPut-action.Description: Copy files to FTP server from a specified destination.

Table-batchsource.Name: Table
Table-batchsource.Description:
Reads the entire contents of a CDAP Table. Outputs one record for each row in the Table.
The Table must conform to a given schema.

OracleExport-action.Name: OracleExport
OracleExport-action.Description:
A Hydrator Action plugin to efficiently export data from Oracle to HDFS or local file system. The plugin uses
Oracle's command line tools to export data. The data exported from this tool can then be used in Hydrator pipelines.

BigQueryMultiTable-batchsink.Name: BigQueryMultiTable
BigQueryMultiTable-batchsink.Description:
This sink writes to a multiple BigQuery tables.
BigQuery is Google's serverless, highly scalable, enterprise data warehouse.
Data is first written to a temporary location on Google Cloud Storage, then loaded into BigQuery from there.

Mysql-postaction.Name: Mysql
Mysql-postaction.Description:
Runs a MySQL query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

Netezza-action.Name: Netezza
Netezza-action.Description: Action that runs a Netezza command.

HTTPCallback-postaction.Name: HTTPCallback
HTTPCallback-postaction.Description: Performs an HTTP request at the end of a pipeline run.

Cassandra-batchsource.Name: Cassandra
Cassandra-batchsource.Description: Batch source to use Apache Cassandra as a source.

SqlServer-batchsource.Name: SqlServer
SqlServer-batchsource.Description:
Reads from a SQL Server using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

GoogleSubscriber-streamingsource.Name: GoogleSubscriber
GoogleSubscriber-streamingsource.Description:
This sources reads from a Google Cloud Pub/Sub subscription in realtime.
Cloud Pub/Sub brings the scalability, flexibility, and reliability of enterprise message-oriented
middleware to the cloud. By providing many-to-many, asynchronous messaging that decouples senders and receivers,
it allows for secure and highly available communication between independently written applications.

Db2-postaction.Name: Db2
Db2-postaction.Description:
Runs a DB2 query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

Netezza-postaction.Name: Netezza
Netezza-postaction.Description:
Runs a Netezza query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

Postgres-postaction.Name: Postgres
Postgres-postaction.Description:
Runs a PostgreSQL query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

Twitter-streamingsource.Name: Twitter
Twitter-streamingsource.Description: Samples tweets in real-time through Spark streaming. Output records will have this schema:

File-streamingsource.Name: File
File-streamingsource.Description:
File streaming source. Watches a directory and streams file contents of any new files added to the directory.
Files must be atomically moved or renamed.

HBase-batchsource.Name: HBase
HBase-batchsource.Description:
Batch source that reads from a column family in an HBase table.
This source differs from the Table source in that it does not use a CDAP dataset,
but reads directly from HBase.

AzureDelete-action.Name: AzureDelete
AzureDelete-action.Description: Azure Delete Action plugin deletes a container on Azure Storage Blob service.

Cassandra-batchsink.Name: Cassandra
Cassandra-batchsink.Description: Batch sink to use Apache Cassandra as a sink.

Mysql-batchsource.Name: Mysql
Mysql-batchsource.Description:
Reads from a MySQL instance using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

Db2-action.Name: Db2
Db2-action.Description: Action that runs a DB2 command.

Projection-transform.Name: Projection
Projection-transform.Description:
The Projection transform lets you drop, keep, rename, and cast fields to a different type.
Fields are first dropped based on the drop or keep field, then cast, then renamed.

RowDenormalizer-batchaggregator.Name: RowDenormalizer
RowDenormalizer-batchaggregator.Description: Converts raw data into denormalized data based on a key column. User is able to specify the list of fields that should be used in the denormalized record, with an option to use an alias for the output field name. For example, 'ADDRESS' in the input is mapped to 'addr' in the output schema.

Db2-batchsink.Name: Db2
Db2-batchsink.Description: Writes records to a DB2 table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

TPFSAvro-batchsource.Name: TPFSAvro
TPFSAvro-batchsource.Description: Reads from a TimePartitionedFileSet whose data is in Avro format.

GCSMove-action.Name: GCSMove
GCSMove-action.Description:
This plugin moves objects from one Google Cloud Storage bucket to another.
A single object can be moved, or a directory of objects can be moved.

Normalize-transform.Name: Normalize
Normalize-transform.Description:
Normalize is a transform plugin that breaks one source row into multiple target rows.
Attributes stored in the columns of a table or a file may need to be broken into multiple
records: for example, one record per column attribute. In general, the plugin allows the
conversion of columns to rows.

XMLReader-batchsource.Name: XMLReader
XMLReader-batchsource.Description: The XML Reader plugin is a source plugin that allows users to read XML files stored on HDFS.

S3-batchsource.Name: S3
S3-batchsource.Description:
This source is used whenever you need to read from Amazon S3.
For example, you may want to read in log files from S3 every hour and then store
the logs in a TimePartitionedFileSet.

ScalaSparkCompute-sparkcompute.Name: ScalaSparkCompute
ScalaSparkCompute-sparkcompute.Description:
Executes user-provided Spark code in Scala that transforms RDD to RDD with full
access to all Spark features.

Postgres-action.Name: Postgres
Postgres-action.Description: Action that runs a PostgreSQL command.

SqlServer-postaction.Name: SqlServer
SqlServer-postaction.Description:
Runs a SQL Server query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

File-batchsink.Name: File
File-batchsink.Description: Writes to a filesystem in various formats format.

SnapshotText-batchsink.Name: SnapshotText
SnapshotText-batchsink.Description:
A batch sink for a PartitionedFileSet that writes snapshots of data as a new
partition. Data is written in Text format.

Salesforce-batchsink.Name: Salesforce
Salesforce-batchsink.Description:
A batch sink that inserts sObjects into Salesforce.
Examples of sObjects are opportunities, contacts, accounts, leads, any custom objects, etc.

StructuredRecordToGenericRecord-transfor.Name: StructuredRecordToGenericRecord
StructuredRecordToGenericRecord-transfor.Description: Transforms a StructuredRecord into an Avro GenericRecord.

SnapshotParquet-batchsource.Name: SnapshotParquet
SnapshotParquet-batchsource.Description:
A batch source that reads from a corresponding SnapshotParquet sink.
The source will only read the most recent snapshot written to the sink.

ADLSDelete-action.Name: ADLSDelete
ADLSDelete-action.Description: Deletes a file or files within ADLS file system.

RecordSplitter-transform.Name: RecordSplitter
RecordSplitter-transform.Description: Given a field and a delimiter, emits one record for each split of the field.

SalesforceMultiObjects-batchsource.Name: SalesforceMultiObjects
SalesforceMultiObjects-batchsource.Description:
This source reads multiple sObjects from Salesforce. The data which should be read is specified using list of sObjects 
and incremental or range date filters. The source will output a record for each row in the SObjects it reads, 
with each record containing an additional field that holds the name of the SObject the record came from. 
In addition, for each SObject that will be read, this plugin will set pipeline arguments where the key is 'multisink.[SObjectName]' 
and the value is the schema of the SObject.

WindowsShareCopy-action.Name: WindowsShareCopy
WindowsShareCopy-action.Description: Copies a file or files on a Microsoft Windows share to an HDFS directory.

DataProfiler-batchaggregator.Name: DataProfiler
DataProfiler-batchaggregator.Description:
Calculates statistics for each input field.
For every field, a total count and null count will be calculated.
For numeric fields, min, max, mean, stddev, zero count, positive count, and negative count will be calculated.
For string fields, min length, max length, mean length, and empty count will be calculated.
For boolean fields, true and false counts will be calculated.
When calculating means, only non-null values are considered.

Oracle-batchsink.Name: Oracle
Oracle-batchsink.Description: Writes records to an Oracle table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

AmazonS3Client-action.Name: AmazonS3Client
AmazonS3Client-action.Description: The Amazon S3 Client Action is used to work with S3 buckets and objects before or after the execution of a pipeline.

Netezza-batchsink.Name: Netezza
Netezza-batchsink.Description: Writes records to a Netezza table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

VerticaBulkImportAction-action.Name: VerticaBulkImportAction
VerticaBulkImportAction-action.Description: Vertica Bulk Import Action plugin gets executed after successful mapreduce or spark job. It reads all the files in a given directory and bulk imports contents of those files into vertica table.

SnapshotAvro-batchsink.Name: SnapshotAvro
SnapshotAvro-batchsink.Description:
A batch sink for a PartitionedFileSet that writes snapshots of data as a new
partition. Data is written in Avro format. A corresponding SnapshotAvro source
can be used to read only the most recently written snapshot.

Netezza-batchsource.Name: Netezza
Netezza-batchsource.Description:
Reads from a Netezza using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

VerticaBulkExportAction-action.Name: VerticaBulkExportAction
VerticaBulkExportAction-action.Description: Bulk exports data in a vertica table into a file.

TopN-batchaggregator.Name: TopN
TopN-batchaggregator.Description: Top-N returns the top "n" records from the input set, based on the criteria specified in the plugin configuration.

JavaScript-transform.Name: JavaScript
JavaScript-transform.Description:
Executes user-provided JavaScript that transforms one record into zero or more records.
Input records are converted into JSON objects which can be directly accessed in
JavaScript. The transform expects to receive a JSON object as input, which it can
process and emit zero or more records or emit error using the provided emitter object.

TMS-alertpublisher.Name: TMS
TMS-alertpublisher.Description:
Publishes alerts to the CDAP Transactional Messaging System (TMS) as json objects. The plugin
allows you to specify the topic and namespace to publish to, as well as a rate limit for the
maximum number of alerts to publish per second.

Salesforce-batchsource.Name: Salesforce
Salesforce-batchsource.Description:
This source reads sObjects from Salesforce.
Examples of sObjects are opportunities, contacts, accounts, leads, any custom object, etc.

ScalaSparkSink-sparksink.Name: ScalaSparkSink
ScalaSparkSink-sparksink.Description:
Executes user-provided Spark code in Scala that operates on an input RDD or Dataframe with full
access to all Spark features.

MultiTableDatabase-batchsource.Name: MultiTableDatabase
MultiTableDatabase-batchsource.Description:
Reads from multiple tables within a database using JDBC. Often used in conjunction with the DynamicMultiFileset sink
to perform dumps from multiple tables to HDFS files in a single pipeline. The source will output a record for each
row in the tables it reads, with each record containing an additional field that holds the name of the table the
record came from. In addition, for each table that will be read, this plugin will set pipeline arguments where the
key is 'multisink.[tablename]' and the value is the schema of the table. This is to make it work with the
DynamicMultiFileset.

FileAppender-batchsink.Name: FileAppender
FileAppender-batchsink.Description:
Writes to a CDAP FileSet in text format. HDFS append must be enabled for this to work.
One line is written for each record sent to the sink.
All record fields are joined using a configurable separator.
Each time a batch is written, the sink will examine all existing files in the output directory.
If there are any files that are smaller in size than the size threshold, or more recent than
the age threshold, new data will be appended to those files instead of written to new files.

AddField-transform.Name: AddField
AddField-transform.Description:
Adds a new field to each record. The field value can either be a new UUID, or it can be set directly through
configuration. This transform is used when you want to add a unique id field to each record, or when you want
to tag each record with some constant value. For example, you may want to add the logical start time as a field
to each record.

Oracle-batchsource.Name: Oracle
Oracle-batchsource.Description:
Reads from an Oracle table using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

GCS-batchsink.Name: GCS
GCS-batchsink.Description:
This plugin writes records to one or more files in a directory on Google Cloud Storage.
Files can be written in various formats such as csv, avro, parquet, and json.

S3ToRedshift-action.Name: S3ToRedshift
S3ToRedshift-action.Description: S3ToRedshift Action that will load the data from AWS S3 bucket into the AWS Redshift table.

Oracle-action.Name: Oracle
Oracle-action.Description: Action that runs an Oracle command.

MultiFieldAdder-transform.Name: MultiFieldAdder
MultiFieldAdder-transform.Description:
Multi Field Adder Transform allows you to add one or more fields to the output.
Each field specified has a name and the value. The value is currently set to
be of type string.

Email-postaction.Name: Email
Email-postaction.Description: Sends an email at the end of a pipeline run.

Wrangler-transform.Name: Wrangler
Wrangler-transform.Description:
This plugin applies data transformation directives on your data records. The directives
are generated either through an interactive user interface or by manual entry into the
plugin.

Elasticsearch-batchsource.Name: Elasticsearch
Elasticsearch-batchsource.Description:
Pulls documents from Elasticsearch according to the query specified by the user and converts each document
to a Structured Record with the fields and schema specified by the user. The Elasticsearch server should
be running prior to creating the application.

Run-transform.Name: Run
Run-transform.Description:
Runs an executable binary which is installed and available on the local filesystem of the Hadoop nodes. Run transform
plugin allows the user to read the structured record as input and returns the output record, to be further processed
downstream in the pipeline.

ValueMapper-transform.Name: ValueMapper
ValueMapper-transform.Description:
Value Mapper is a transform plugin that maps string values of a field in the input record
to a mapping value using a mapping dataset.

AzureDecompress-action.Name: AzureDecompress
AzureDecompress-action.Description: Azure decompress Action plugin decompress gz files from a container on Azure Storage Blob service into another container.

FailPipeline-batchsink.Name: FailPipeline
FailPipeline-batchsink.Description:
Batch Sink is used to fail the running pipeline when any of the record flows to this sink on receiving
the first record itself.

NGramTransform-sparkcompute.Name: NGramTransform
NGramTransform-sparkcompute.Description: Transforms the input features into n-grams, where n-gram is a sequence of n tokens (typically words) for some integer 'n'.

Spanner-batchsink.Name: Spanner
Spanner-batchsink.Description:
This sink writes to a Google Cloud Spanner table.
Cloud Spanner is a fully managed, mission-critical, relational database service that offers transactional
consistency at global scale, schemas, SQL (ANSI 2011 with extensions),
and automatic, synchronous replication for high availability.

ArgumentSetter-action.Name: ArgumentSetter
ArgumentSetter-action.Description: Performs an HTTP request to fetch arguments to set in the pipeline.

Table-batchsink.Name: Table
Table-batchsink.Description:
Writes records to a CDAP Table with one record field mapping
to the Table rowkey, and all other record fields mapping to Table columns.

DynamicMultiFileset-batchsink.Name: DynamicMultiFileset
DynamicMultiFileset-batchsink.Description:
This plugin is normally used in conjunction with the MultiTableDatabase batch source to write records from multiple
databases into multiple filesets in text format. Each fileset it writes to will contain a single 'ingesttime' partition,
which will contain the logical start time of the pipeline run. The plugin expects that the filsets it needs to write
to will be set as pipeline arguments, where the key is 'multisink.[fileset]' and the value is the fileset schema.
Normally, you rely on the MultiTableDatabase source to set those pipeline arguments, but they can also be manually
set or set by an Action plugin in your pipeline. The sink will expect each record to contain a special split field
that will be used to determine which records are written to each fileset. For example, suppose the
the split field is 'tablename'. A record whose 'tablename' field is set to 'activity' will be written to the 'activity'
fileset.

GCSCopy-action.Name: GCSCopy
GCSCopy-action.Description:
This plugin copies objects from one Google Cloud Storage bucket to another.
A single object can be copied, or a directory of objects can be copied.

Mysql-batchsink.Name: Mysql
Mysql-batchsink.Description: Writes records to a MySQL table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

Cube-batchsink.Name: Cube
Cube-batchsink.Description: Batch sink that writes data to a Cube dataset.

Oracle-postaction.Name: Oracle
Oracle-postaction.Description:
Runs an Oracle query at the end of the pipeline run.
Can be configured to run only on success, only on failure, or always at the end of the run.

LogParser-transform.Name: LogParser
LogParser-transform.Description:
Parses logs from any input source for relevant information such as URI, IP,
browser, device, HTTP status code, and timestamp.

GCSBucketCreate-action.Name: GCSBucketCreate
GCSBucketCreate-action.Description:
This plugin creates objects in a Google Cloud Storage bucket.
Cloud Storage allows world-wide storage and retrieval of any amount of data at any time.

Database-action.Name: Database
Database-action.Description: Action that runs a database command.

Kafka-batchsource.Name: Kafka
Kafka-batchsource.Description:
Kafka batch source. Emits the record from kafka. It will emit a record based on the schema and format 
you use, or if no schema or format is specified, the message payload will be emitted. The source will 
remember the offset it read last run and continue from that offset for the next run.
The Kafka batch source supports providing additional kafka properties for the kafka consumer, 
reading from kerberos-enabled kafka and limiting the number of records read. This plugin uses kafka 0.10.2 java apis.

XMLParser-transform.Name: XMLParser
XMLParser-transform.Description:
The XML Parser Transform uses XPath to extract fields from a complex XML event. This plugin should generally be used
in conjunction with the XML Reader Batch Source. The XML Reader will provide individual events to the XML Parser,
which will be responsible for extracting fields from the events and mapping them to the output schema.

KVTable-batchsource.Name: KVTable
KVTable-batchsource.Description:
Reads the entire contents of a KeyValueTable, outputting records with a 'key' field and a
'value' field. Both fields are of type bytes.

ADLSBatchSink-batchsink.Name: ADLSBatchSink
ADLSBatchSink-batchsink.Description: Azure Data Lake Store Batch Sink writes data to Azure Data Lake Store directory in avro, orc or text format.

KinesisSource-streamingsource.Name: KinesisSource
KinesisSource-streamingsource.Description: Spark streaming source that reads from AWS Kinesis streams.

CloneRecord-transform.Name: CloneRecord
CloneRecord-transform.Description:
Makes a copy of every input record received for a configured number of times on the output. 
This transform does not change any record fields or types. It's an identity transform.

GCSBucketDelete-action.Name: GCSBucketDelete
GCSBucketDelete-action.Description:
This plugin deletes objects in a Google Cloud Storage bucket.
Cloud Storage allows world-wide storage and retrieval of any amount of data at any time.

Db2-batchsource.Name: Db2
Db2-batchsource.Description:
Reads from a DB2 using a configurable SQL query.
Outputs one record for each row returned by the query.

SqlServer-batchsink.Name: SqlServer
SqlServer-batchsink.Description: Writes records to a SQL Server table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

Salesforce-streamingsource.Name: Salesforce
Salesforce-streamingsource.Description:
This source tracks updates in Salesforce sObjects.
Examples of sObjects are opportunities, contacts, accounts, leads, any custom object, etc.

SnapshotAvro-batchsource.Name: SnapshotAvro
SnapshotAvro-batchsource.Description:
A batch source that reads from a corresponding SnapshotAvro sink.
The source will only read the most recent snapshot written to the sink.

Compressor-transform.Name: Compressor
Compressor-transform.Description:
Compresses configured fields. Multiple fields can be specified to be compressed using different compression algorithms.
Plugin supports SNAPPY, ZIP, and GZIP types of compression of fields.

BigQueryTable-batchsource.Name: BigQueryTable
BigQueryTable-batchsource.Description:
This source reads the entire contents of a BigQuery table.
BigQuery is Google's serverless, highly scalable, enterprise data warehouse.
Data from the BigQuery table is first exported to a temporary location on Google Cloud Storage,
then read into the pipeline from there.

SalesforceDataExtension-batchsink.Name: SalesforceDataExtension
SalesforceDataExtension-batchsink.Description:
This sink inserts records into a Salesforce Marketing Cloud Data Extension.
The sink requires Server-to-Server integration with the Salesforce Marketing Cloud API. See
https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.mc-app-development.meta/mc-app-development/api-integration.htm
for more information about creating an API integration.

GCSMultiFiles-batchsink.Name: GCSMultiFiles
GCSMultiFiles-batchsink.Description:
This plugin is normally used in conjunction with the MultiTableDatabase batch source to write records from multiple
databases into multiple directories in various formats. The plugin expects that the directories it needs to write to
will be set as pipeline arguments, where the key is 'multisink.[directory]' and the value is the schema of the data.

File-batchsource.Name: File
File-batchsource.Description:
This source is used whenever you need to read from a distributed file system.
For example, you may want to read in log files from S3 every hour and then store
the logs in a TimePartitionedFileSet.

Elasticsearch-batchsink.Name: Elasticsearch
Elasticsearch-batchsink.Description:
Takes the Structured Record from the input source and converts it to a JSON string, then indexes it in
Elasticsearch using the index, type, and idField specified by the user. The Elasticsearch server should
be running prior to creating the application.

PythonEvaluator-transform.Name: PythonEvaluator
PythonEvaluator-transform.Description:
Executes user-provided python code that transforms one record into zero or more records.
Each input record is converted into a dictionary which can be directly accessed in
python. The transform expects to receive a dictionary as input, which it can
process and emit zero or more transformed dictionaries, or emit an error dictionary using the provided emitter object.

Database-batchsink.Name: Database
Database-batchsink.Description: Writes records to a database table. Each record will be written to a row in the table.

Trash-batchsink.Name: Trash
Trash-batchsink.Description:
Trash consumes all the records on the input and eats them all,
means no output is generated or no output is stored anywhere.

UnionSplitter-splittertransform.Name: UnionSplitter
UnionSplitter-splittertransform.Description: The union splitter is used to split data by a union schema, so that type specific logic can be done downstream.

MLPredictor-sparkcompute.Name: MLPredictor
MLPredictor-sparkcompute.Description:
Uses a model trained by the ModelTrainer plugin to add a prediction field to incoming records.
The same features used to train the model must be present in each input record, but input records can also
contain additional non-feature fields. If the trained model uses categorical features,
and if the record being predicted contains new categories, that record will be dropped.
For example, suppose categorical feature 'city' was used to train a model that predicts housing prices.
If an incoming record has 'New York' as the city, but 'New York' was not in the training set,
that record will be dropped.

HTTP-batchsink.Name: HTTP
HTTP-batchsink.Description: Sink plugin to send the messages from the pipeline to an external http endpoint.

DynTable-batchsink.Name: DynTable
DynTable-batchsink.Description: This plugin supports writing dynamic schemas record to CDAP Dataset Table. In addition to writing dynamic schema tables, it also support regular structured records to be written to Tables.

FTPCopy-action.Name: FTPCopy
FTPCopy-action.Description: Copy files from FTP server to the specified destination.

Datastore-batchsink.Name: Datastore
Datastore-batchsink.Description:
This sink writes data to Google Cloud Datastore.
Datastore is a NoSQL document database built for automatic scaling and high performance.

JSONParser-transform.Name: JSONParser
JSONParser-transform.Description:
Parses an input JSON event into a record. The input JSON event could be either a map of
string fields to values or it could be a complex nested JSON structure. The plugin allows you
to express JSON paths for extracting fields from complex nested input JSON.

FileContents-action.Name: FileContents
FileContents-action.Description:
This action plugin can be used to check if a file is empty or if the
contents of a file match a given pattern.

Datastore-batchsource.Name: Datastore
Datastore-batchsource.Description:
This source reads data from Google Cloud Datastore.
Datastore is a NoSQL document database built for automatic scaling and high performance.

SnapshotParquet-batchsink.Name: SnapshotParquet
SnapshotParquet-batchsink.Description:
A batch sink for a PartitionedFileSet that writes snapshots of data as a new
partition. Data is written in Parquet format. A corresponding SnapshotParquet source
can be used to read only the most recently written snapshot.

SSH-action.Name: SSH
SSH-action.Description: Establishes an SSH connection with remote machine to execute command on that machine.

Decryptor-transform.Name: Decryptor
Decryptor-transform.Description:
Decrypts one or more fields in input records using a keystore 
that must be present on all nodes of the cluster.

Mysql-action.Name: Mysql
Mysql-action.Description: Action that runs a MySQL command.

TPFSParquet-batchsource.Name: TPFSParquet
TPFSParquet-batchsource.Description: Reads from a TimePartitionedFileSet whose data is in Parquet format.

ErrorCollector-errortransform.Name: ErrorCollector
ErrorCollector-errortransform.Description:
The ErrorCollector plugin takes errors emitted from the previous stage and flattens them by adding
the error message, code, and stage to the record and outputting the result.

BigQueryTable-batchsink.Name: BigQueryTable
BigQueryTable-batchsink.Description:
This sink writes to a BigQuery table.
BigQuery is Google's serverless, highly scalable, enterprise data warehouse.
Data is first written to a temporary location on
Google Cloud Storage, then loaded into BigQuery from there.

Validator-transform.Name: Validator
Validator-transform.Description:
Validates a record, writing to an error dataset if the record is invalid.
Otherwise it passes the record on to the next stage.

HTTPToHDFS-action.Name: HTTPToHDFS
HTTPToHDFS-action.Description: Action to fetch data from an external http endpoint and create a file in HDFS.

Sampling-batchaggregator.Name: Sampling
Sampling-batchaggregator.Description:
Sampling a large dataset flowing through this plugin to pull random records. Supports two types of sampling
i.e, Systematic Sampling and Reservoir Sampling.

HBase-batchsink.Name: HBase
HBase-batchsink.Description:
Writes records to a column family in an HBase table with one record field mapping
to the rowkey, and all other record fields mapping to table column qualifiers.
This sink differs from the Table sink in that it does not use CDAP datasets, but writes
to HBase directly.

ScalaSparkProgram-sparkprogram.Name: ScalaSparkProgram
ScalaSparkProgram-sparkprogram.Description: Executes user-provided Spark code in Scala.
